ink\";s:85:\"http://cdn.update.time.ly/packages/all-in-one-event-calendar-extended-views_1.2.0.zip\";s:8:\"sections\";a:2:{s:11:\"description\";s:37:\"Get the best looking website calendar\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:2027:\"<strong>1.2</strong>\r\n<strong>Improvements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n       <li>Multiday events now show start and end date in posterboard view</li> \r\n       <li>For Hubs- Venues can now be Replaced with a Custom Filter in event title</li>\r\n       <li>Improved Posterboard loading speed</li>\r\n       <li>Showing end date for multidate events on Posterboard</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.4</strong>\r\n<strong>Bugs</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n     <li>Fixed a JavaScript error that could occur when Posterboard tiles are forced to a grid</li>\r\n     <li>Fixed a conflict with the Gantry theme</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.3</strong>\r\n<strong>Improvements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n     <li>Improved events rendering on posterboard</li>\r\n     <li>Event detail pages will load in a modal when opened from a calendar embedded using the SuperWidget</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.2</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Improved version checking</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed a link that pointed to the originating site, rather than opening within the widget</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed a JavaScript issue experienced by some users where the calendar wasn\'t correctly initialized and rendered some actions unusable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.1</strong>\r\n* Posterboard tiles may now optionally be a fixed height, to form a grid\r\n* Improved translations\r\n* Added Extended Views to Widget Creator \r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.0</strong>\r\nversion bump\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.10</strong>\r\nMade it possible to translate view names (Posterboard, Stream)\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.9</strong>\r\nAdded ability to display multiple calendars on a single page\r\nImproved mobile devices compatibility\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.8</strong>\r\nFixed issue where Streamview wasn\'t reflecting category colours properly;\r\nAdded shortcodes description for views defined in Extended Views;\r\nFixed rendering in Super Widget mode;\r\nIntroduced minimum Core version check for forwards compatibility;\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.7</strong>\r\nFixed licence activation issue\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.6</strong>\r\nupdated localization files\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.5</strong>\r\nFixed issue with category tags in PosterBoard view.\";}s:6:\"author\";s:65:\"<a href=\"https://time.ly\" target=\"_blank\">Timely Network Inc.</a>\";}s:97:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-frontend-submissions/all-in-one-event-calendar-frontend-submissions.php\";a:11:{s:6:\"plugin\";s:97:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-frontend-submissions/all-in-one-event-calendar-frontend-submissions.php\";s:11:\"new_version\";s:5:\"1.2.0\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"1.2.0\";s:4:\"name\";s:20:\"Frontend Submissions\";s:4:\"slug\";s:46:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-frontend-submissions\";s:3:\"url\";s:15:\"https://time.ly\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:15:\"https://time.ly\";s:7:\"package\";s:91:\"http://cdn.update.time.ly/packages/all-in-one-event-calendar-frontend-submissions_1.2.0.zip\";s:13:\"download_link\";s:91:\"http://cdn.update.time.ly/packages/all-in-one-event-calendar-frontend-submissions_1.2.0.zip\";s:8:\"sections\";a:2:{s:11:\"description\";s:109:\"Frontend submissions allows your community, including anonymous members, to submit events to your calendar.  \";s:9:\"changelog\";s:2606:\"<Strong>1.2</strong>\r\n<strong>Improvements</strong>	\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Renamed the field \"external URL\". It is now \"Website URL\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Fixes</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Some dates weren\'t correctly processed for front-end submissions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.4</strong>\r\n<strong>Bugs</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Fixed JavaScript loading. New changes introduced in All-in-One Event Calendar v2.2.0 weren\'t fully taken into account and some files left ignored thus rendering plugin unusable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.3</strong>\r\n<strong>Features</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Filter Groups are now available on the form for event creators to select</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>Improvements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Improved URLs handling when WordPress is upgraded to use SSL addresses</li>\r\n   <li>Improved settings page</li>\r\n   <li>Price is required by default (free is no longer \"on\" by default)</li>\r\n   <li>It is now possible to require image to be attached</li>\r\n   <li>It\'s now possible to choose from classical reCAPTCHA and new NoCAPTCHA by Google</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.2</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Fixed a JavaScript issue experienced by some users where the calendar wasn\'t correctly initialized and rendered some actions unusable</li>\r\n   <li>Resolved conflict with Divi theme</li>\r\n   <li>fixed end date issue when an event has no end time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.0</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Fixed issue where submitting a feed disabled the calendar</li>\r\n   <li>Improved handling of strings for translations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.0</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Made it possible to choose event timezone on front-end when submitting new event</li>\r\n   <li>Giving site admins option to automatically publish anonymously submitted events</li>\r\n   <li>Allowing to edit date/time values manually</li>\r\n   <li>Fixed \"Post Your Event\" button alignment in filter menu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>1.0.11</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Improved mobile devices compatibility</li>\r\n	<li>Allow automatic publishing of submitted events</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>1.0.10</strong>\r\nFront end submissions:\r\n* Changed labels to read \"(required)\"\r\n* Make all fields always visible;\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.9</strong>\r\nRestored feature to send email notification to site admin when new event is submitted;\r\nAdded default image to front-end submission form to show when none is selected;\r\nRestore disclaimer checkbox;\r\nFixed required fields behaviour - required fields cannot be omitted now;\r\nIntroduced minimum Core version check for forwards compatibility;\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.8</strong>\r\nFixed licence activation issue\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.7</strong>\r\nInitial release\";}s:6:\"author\";s:65:\"<a href=\"https://time.ly\" target=\"_blank\">Timely Network Inc.</a>\";}s:81:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-super-widget/all-in-one-event-calendar-super-widget.php\";a:11:{s:6:\"plugin\";s:81:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-super-widget/all-in-one-event-calendar-super-widget.php\";s:11:\"new_version\";s:7:\"1.1.0.3\";s:7:\"version\";s:7:\"1.1.0.3\";s:4:\"name\";s:11:\"SuperWidget\";s:4:\"slug\";s:38:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-super-widget\";s:3:\"url\";s:15:\"https://time.ly\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:15:\"https://time.ly\";s:7:\"package\";s:85:\"http://cdn.update.time.ly/packages/all-in-one-event-calendar-super-widget_1.1.0.3.zip\";s:13:\"download_link\";s:85:\"http://cdn.update.time.ly/packages/all-in-one-event-calendar-super-widget_1.1.0.3.zip\";s:8:\"sections\";a:2:{s:11:\"description\";s:105:\"SuperWidget allows you to embed your full calendar or a filtered calendar anywhere, even on other sites. \";s:9:\"changelog\";s:1247:\"<strong>1.1</strong>\r\n<strong>Improvements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Improved calendar embedding options by making it more compatible with different platforms</li>\r\n   <li>Event details are now always loaded in SuperWidget instead of redirecting visitor to main site</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.9</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Improved version checking</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed a link that pointed to the originating site, rather than opening within the widget</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed a JavaScript issue experienced by some users where the calendar wasn\'t correctly initialized and rendered some actions unusable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.8</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Two Widgets can now be embedded on the same page</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed issue with view switching</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed theme conflict with default hosted calendar theme</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.7</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Fixed AJAX navigation behaviour</li>\r\n	<li>Starting to support multiple calendars on a single page</li>\r\n	<li>Improved settings page for Super Widget</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>1.0.6</strong>\r\nFixed issue where some features weren\'t working;\r\nIntroduced minimum Core version check for forwards compatibility;\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.5</strong>\r\nFixed licence activation issue\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.4</strong>\r\nInitial release\";}s:6:\"author\";s:65:\"<a href=\"https://time.ly\" target=\"_blank\">Timely Network Inc.</a>\";}s:95:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-twitter-integration/all-in-one-event-calendar-twitter-integration.php\";a:11:{s:6:\"plugin\";s:95:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-twitter-integration/all-in-one-event-calendar-twitter-integration.php\";s:11:\"new_version\";s:5:\"1.1.4\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"1.1.4\";s:4:\"name\";s:7:\"Twitter\";s:4:\"slug\";s:45:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-twitter-integration\";s:3:\"url\";s:15:\"https://time.ly\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:15:\"https://time.ly\";s:7:\"package\";s:90:\"http://cdn.update.time.ly/packages/all-in-one-event-calendar-twitter-integration_1.1.4.zip\";s:13:\"download_link\";s:90:\"http://cdn.update.time.ly/packages/all-in-one-event-calendar-twitter-integration_1.1.4.zip\";s:8:\"sections\";a:2:{s:11:\"description\";s:85:\"Connect your calendar to Twitter to automatically or manually Tweet out your events. \";s:9:\"changelog\";s:1086:\"<strong>1.1.3</strong>\r\n<strong>Improvements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Added setting to Tweet events by default</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.2</strong>\r\n<strong>Improvements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Improved URLs handling when WordPress is upgraded to use SSL addresses</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.1</strong>\r\n* Improved Twitter messages formatting: stripping metadata (hashtags, location information) until it fits, use short, instead of full, date format in tweets\r\n* Make it possible to reference latitude/longitude in list views\r\n* Improved Twitter warning msg for unconnected installations\r\n\r\n<strong>1.1.0</strong>\r\n* Improved authentication process - displays information about success of authentication;\r\n* Improved logging - display notice after event has been processed (display error message if sending failed, or link to tweet if it has been successfully posted);\r\n* Started collecting information about all tweets processing;\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.7</strong>\r\nFixed app activation link\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.6</strong>\r\nFixed licence activation issue\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.5</strong>\r\nInitial Release\";}s:6:\"author\";s:65:\"<a href=\"https://time.ly\" target=\"_blank\">Timely Network Inc.</a>\";}s:67:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-venue/all-in-one-event-calendar-venue.php\";a:11:{s:6:\"plugin\";s:67:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-venue/all-in-one-event-calendar-venue.php\";s:11:\"new_version\";s:5:\"1.1.0\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"1.1.0\";s:4:\"name\";s:6:\"Venues\";s:4:\"slug\";s:31:\"all-in-one-event-calendar-venue\";s:3:\"url\";s:15:\"https://time.ly\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:15:\"https://time.ly\";s:7:\"package\";s:76:\"http://cdn.update.time.ly/packages/all-in-one-event-calendar-venue_1.1.0.zip\";s:13:\"download_link\";s:76:\"http://cdn.update.time.ly/packages/all-in-one-event-calendar-venue_1.1.0.zip\";s:8:\"sections\";a:2:{s:11:\"description\";s:144:\"If you have events occurring in different locales Venues helps speed the event creation process by letting you save detailed Venue information. \";s:9:\"changelog\";s:1221:\"<Strong>1.1</strong>\r\n<strong>Improvements</strong>	\r\n<ul>	\r\n	<li>Renamed the field \"external URL\". It is now \"Website URL\"</li>\r\n	<li>Removed \"show map\" setting</li>\r\n	<li>Improved Translations</li> \r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>Fixes</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Now properly detecting system errors during avatar creation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>1.0.18</strong>\r\n<strong>Improvements</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n   <li>Imported events will now create a Venue if there are venue details available</li>\r\n   