(172,1,'2014-07-15 19:30:00','2014-07-15 19:30:00','<span class=\"highlight2\">At SEED SPOT, we\'ve seen a thousand stories of aspirational entrepreneurs. We\'re happy to share a few.</span> Our founder and CEO, Courtney Klein, is a nationally renowned speaker whose stories of determination and accomplishment leave audiences inspired and engaged. She loves to tell stories, including her own, which includes founding her first nonprofit at the age of 21. She also loves to tell the stories of SEED SPOT ventures, and the real journey that it takes to create impact through entrepreneurship.\n\n<span class=\"highlight2\">People like to be challenged - Courtney does a great job pushing their limits while making people feel good about their work.</span> It\'s important to accept that change needs to be made in the world. It\'s equally important to question how we are all contributing the greater whole. Courtney challenges small and large audiences to think critically about their own path, passion, and journey to leave an impact. Courtney brings some of these issues to life and highlights<em>solutions</em> to social problems in ways that excite and inspire people.\n\n<span class=\"highlight2\">Affordable, experienced, and tailored to your event.</span> Because Courtney and SEED SPOT are on a mission to grow social entrepreneurship worldwide, we keep speaking fees affordable. Courtney has spoken at a wide range of events including anExecutive Education program in Australia, a commencement address at St. Mary\'s University, Keynotes at the World Affairs Council and Spirit of Service Symposium for Fortune 500 companies, and tons of stuff in between. She loves diverse audiences.\n\n<span class=\"highlight2\">More about Courtney Klein</span> Courtney is an Arizona native and graduate of Arizona State University where she received her undergraduate and masters degrees in Nonprofit Management. Previously, Courtney served as the Co-Founder &amp; CEO of New Global Citizens, the result of a nonprofit organization she launched in her senior year of college on a $1,000 seed grant with a mission to educate, empower, and invest in young people to change the world. New Global Citizens now serves youth in 14 states across the country and works with grassroots partners in over 30 countries around the world. Additionally, Courtney worked as the Director of Strategic Planning &amp; Development for the Greater Phoenix Economic Council.\n\nIn 2011, Courtney was recognized by Splashlife Magazine as one of the nations top 30 Civic Leaders under the age of 30. In 2009, Courtney was named One of 12 Women Who Move the Valley by Arizona Foothills Magazine. In 2008, Courtney received the first Athena Award for young professionals, and was honored by bizAZ as one of 35 Entrepreneurs under 35. In 2007 she was named one of 20 Women to Change Arizona by 2020 by Arizona Woman Magazine and the Arizona Republic. In 2006, Courtney was profiled in the Arizona Republic as one of Arizonas most intriguing Chief Executives, highlighted as one of the six to watch. Additionally, she was honored by the Phoenix Business Journals Power Book as a Power Generation Up-and-Coming Leader. In 2005, Courtney was honored as a Hon Kachina Honoree and in 2002 was named Woman of the Year by the Diocese of Phoenix.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a class=\"button\" style=\"background-color: #de1616;\" href=\"mailto:corinn@seedspot.org\">EMAIL US TO BOOK COURTNEY AS A SPEAKER</a>','COURTNEY KLEIN - SPEAKING CONSULTING','','publish','closed','closed','','courtney-klein-speaking-consulting-2','','','2014-07-15 19:30:00','2014-07-15 19:30:00','',0,'http://seedspot.wpengine.com/?page_id=172',0,'page','',0),
