(1075,1,'2014-05-21 09:40:14','2014-05-21 16:40:14','<a href=\"http://aztechbeat.com/2014/05/seed-spot-summer-program/\">Read the original story here.</a>\n<h1 class=\"blogtitle entry-title\">Seed Spot launches entrepreneur program for high school students</h1>\n<div><a class=\"lightbox-image\" title=\"\" data-rel=\"lightbox\"><img class=\"img-frame \" src=\"http://www.seedspot.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-shot-2015-06-24-at-2.29.52-PM.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\nFrom lemonade stands and dog walking services to building apps or a robotic toy, the entrepreneurial mindset is occurring at a younger age. This summer, parents might wonder how to continue to nurture their childs mindset in a social conscious environment. Seed Spot, a nonprofit incubator dedicated to early-stage community-focused social startups, has launched a new entrepreneurial program for high school students that have a thirst for creativity and innovation.\n\n<!--more-->\n\nThe Seed Spot High School Program is a one-week program designed to inspire, educate and launch solutions to important societal problems. Join the Seed Spot staff, ventures, mentors and a team of like-minded peers for a fun, fast-paced week!\n\nThe deadline to apply is June 6, 2014 and there are two programs available this summer: July 14-18 and July 28-August 1','AZ Tech Beat: SEED SPOT launches entrepreneur program for high school students','','publish','closed','closed','','az-tech-beat-seed-spot-launches-entrepreneur-program-for-high-school-students','','','2014-05-21 09:40:14','2014-05-21 16:40:14','',0,'http://www.seedspot.org/?p=1075',0,'post','',0),
