(1079,1,'2014-05-23 09:56:35','2014-05-23 16:56:35','<div><a class=\"lightbox-image\" title=\"\" data-rel=\"lightbox\"><img class=\"img-frame \" src=\"http://www.seedspot.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-shot-2015-06-24-at-2.37.33-PM-1.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></div>\n<div></div>\n<a href=\"http://frontdoorsnews.com/2014/05/seed-spot-hosts-third-demo-day/\">Read the original article here.</a><!--more-->\n<h1 class=\"headline\">SEED SPOT Hosts Third Demo Day</h1>\nEver wanted to be in the studio audience of the hit entrepreneurial TV show, Shark Tank? On Thursday, June 5, SEED SPOT will offer a somewhat similar experience at its third Demo Day event, which will be held at the Orpheum Theatre. This uplifting entrepreneurial event, which is free and open-to-the-public, will offer just as much energy and excitement as the popular TV show  without the dramatic and outspoken sharks or requests for capital.\n<div id=\"content-area\">\n\nThats because, instead of pitching sharks, 12 SEED SPOT entrepreneurs will be sharing their socially-responsible, purpose-driven business plans with an audience of more than 700 people  who get to vote via text message, in real time, for their favorite venture who will then receive a $5,000 cash prize.\n\nCome watch these Arizona-based entrepreneurs pitch their solutions to important societal problems at SEED SPOTs free Demo Day event from 5:30 p.m. to 7:30 p.m. Each SEED SPOT entrepreneur has three minutes to share his/her business plan, successes and next steps. To prepare for Demo Day, the 12 entrepreneurs went through a rigorous four-month entrepreneurship program. Those that were selected to participate in Demo Day have worked hard to validate that they have customers and a solid business\nmodel.\n\nVentures vary from a mobile-based tool that helps to diagnose epilepsy and an after-school skateboard program for under-served youth, to a kid-friendly product line that combats childhood obesity and a company that helps others create sustainable food gardens. After the short presentations, every audience member gets to vote via text message for their favorite venture.\n\n<strong>SEED SPOT will then announce and award prizes on the spot, including:</strong>\n\n Six months of free office space to a deserving entrepreneur, from SEED SPOT\n $25,000 in cash prizes, courtesy of the Pakis Center for Business Philanthropy\n A $5,000 cash prize to the entrepreneur who receives the highest percentage of audience votes\n\n</div>\n<div id=\"author-info\"></div>','frontdoors news: SEED SPOT Hosts third DEMO DAY','','publish','closed','closed','','1079','','','2014-05-23 09:56:35','2014-05-23 16:56:35','',0,'http://www.seedspot.org/?p=1079',0,'post','',0),
