(1444,1,'2015-02-17 14:29:12','2015-02-17 21:29:12','<div><a class=\"lightbox-image\" title=\"\" href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-shot-2015-06-25-at-12.00.20-PM.png\" data-rel=\"lightbox\"><img class=\"img-frame \" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-shot-2015-06-25-at-12.00.20-PM.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"649\" height=\"415\" /></a></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><a href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/phoenix/news/2015/02/17/seed-spot-receives-100k-grant-to-expand-efforts.html\">Read the original article here.</a></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>By Brandon Brown</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n<p class=\"content__segment\">Phoenix-based Seed Spot received a $100,000 grant from the charitable wing of New York-based investment firm <a class=\"saveLink\" href=\"http://www.bizjournals.com/profiles/company/us/ny/new_york/blackstone_group_lp/3289721\">Blackstone</a> (NYSE: BX) to help expand its incubator model into Phoenix\'s Hispanic community through targeted recruitment and marketing efforts.</p>\n\n</div>\n<!--more-->\n<div>\n<p class=\"content__segment\">Seed Spot was one of 20 organizations that received part of a $3 million initiative from Blackstone Charitable Foundation. The program focuses on funding nonprofits that strengthen entrepreneurial ecosystems and support high-growth entrepreneurs. Seed Spot competed with more than 550 nonprofits from around the world for the grant.</p>\n<p class=\"content__segment\">With its grant money, Seed Spot will diversify its recruitment efforts and expand its high school program.</p>\n\n<aside id=\"module1Mbox\" class=\"inset inset--major hidden--print\">\n<div class=\"module module--ruled\">\n<div class=\"module__header module__header--ruled\">\n<div class=\"pull-right\">Here are the other nonprofits receiving Blackstone funds:</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</aside>\n<ul class=\"content__segment\">\n	<li>Accion US Network (New York), $150,000</li>\n	<li>African Leadership Academy (Johannesburg, South Africa), $150,000</li>\n	<li>Bethnal Green Ventures (London), $150,000</li>\n	<li>Black Founders (San Francisco), $100,000</li>\n	<li>Coalition for Queens (Queens, New York), $175,000</li>\n	<li>Cornell Tech (New York), $200,000</li>\n	<li>Energy Excelerator (Honolulu), $100,000</li>\n	<li>Enterprise Institute (Brookings, South Dakota), $100,000</li>\n	<li>Idea Village (New Orleans), $125,000</li>\n	<li>Launch Tennessee (Nashville), $250,000</li>\n	<li>MaroonX Accelerator (Starksville, Mississippi, and College Station, Texas), $200,000</li>\n	<li>MyBnk (London), $100,000</li>\n	<li>Seeds of Peace (Middle East and Washington), $50,000</li>\n	<li>Social Enterprise Greenhouse (Providence, Rhode Island), $200,000</li>\n	<li>TechnoServe (Mumbai), $150,000</li>\n	<li>Telluride Venture Accelerator (Telluride, Colorado), $125,000</li>\n	<li>Tumml (San Francisco), $175,000</li>\n	<li>UP Global (Seattle), $200,000</li>\n	<li>Venture for America (New York and Philadelphia), $200,000</li>\n</ul>\n</div>','Phoenix Business Journal: SEED SPOT Receives $100k Grant to Expand Efforts into Latino Community','','publish','closed','closed','','phoenix-business-journal-seed-spot-receives-100k-grant-to-expand-efforts-into-latino-community','','','2015-02-17 14:29:12','2015-02-17 21:29:12','',0,'http://www.seedspot.org/?p=1444',0,'post','',0),
