(1448,1,'2015-02-19 14:42:48','2015-02-19 21:42:48','<div><a class=\"lightbox-image\" title=\"\" href=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-shot-2015-06-25-at-12.10.36-PM-1.png\" data-rel=\"lightbox\"><img class=\"img-frame \" src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-shot-2015-06-25-at-12.10.36-PM-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"754\" height=\"505\" /></a></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div>by Jesse A. Millard</div>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n\nFrom the top of a rooftop overlooking downtown Phoenix, Seed Spot announced the nine new startup ventures who have been inducted into Spring 2015s incubator program.\n\nTo kick it off, Seed Spot CEO and co-founder Courtney Klein spoke briefly about her incubator, which has seen an 88 percent success rate of startups who have been brought up through Seed Spotwhich has led to the creation of 160 jobs.\n\n<!--more-->\nWere about making an impact, Klein said.\n<div id=\"gallery-16821-1-slideshow\" class=\"slideshow-window jetpack-slideshow slideshow-black\" data-width=\"580\" data-height=\"410\" data-trans=\"fade\" data-gallery=\"[{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_30.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16829&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Deanna Montrose, gLOVE Treat&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Deanna Montrose, gLOVE Treat&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_9.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16850&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SeedSpot_9&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Mayor Stanton u0026#038; Courtney&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_16.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16843&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SeedSpot_16&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_19.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16840&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SeedSpot_19&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_13.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16846&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Mayor Greg Stanton&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Mayor Greg Stanton &quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_25.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16834&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Ron Wittenberg, HUYA&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Ron Wittenberg, HUYA&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_23.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16836&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SeedSpot_23&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_26.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16833&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Danna Evans, AZ Vision and Hearing&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Danna Evans, AZ Vision and Hearing&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_27.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16832&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Chelsea Harden, H.E.A.R.T. Center&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Chelsea Harden, H.E.A.R.T. Center&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_32.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16827&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;(not full time, donu0026#8217;t use)&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Nicole Cottrell&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_31.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16828&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Dave Leedy, Zombie Box&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Dave Leedy, Zombie Box&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_28.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16831&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Sara Henry, Wellness Lifestyle&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Sara Henry, Wellness Lifestyle&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_24.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16835&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Tishin Donkersley and Mayor Greg Stanton&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Tishin Donkersley and Mayor Greg Stanton&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_33.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16826&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Sheila Iyengar, Nagi Foundation&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Sheila Iyengar, Nagi Foundation&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_34.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16825&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Tara Briscoe, Ryan Mores, Kevin Keleher, Greenlight Solutions&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Tara Briscoe, Ryan Mores, Kevin Keleher, Greenlight Solutions&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_35.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16824&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Mo Joe Ghani, The Genius Factory&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Mo Joe Ghani, The Genius Factory&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_20.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16839&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SeedSpot_20&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;},{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_15.jpg&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;16844&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;SeedSpot_15&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;}]\">\n<div class=\"slideshow-slide\">\n\n<img class=\"\" title=\"Deanna Montrose, gLOVE Treat\" src=\"http://aztechbeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/SeedSpot_30.jpg?w=580\" alt=\"\" width=\"734\" height=\"460\" align=\"middle\" /><span class=\"slideshow-line-height-hack\"></span>\n<div class=\"slideshow-slide-caption\">Deanna Montrose, gLOVE Treat</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"slideshow-controls\"></div>\n</div>\nSeed Spotis a Phoenix based incubator program, which puts early stage ventures and their entrepreneurs through a rigorous curriculum to help build their business.\n\nPhoenix Mayor Greg Stanton spoke at the event and welcomed in the inductees.What youre doing is putting us on the map, he said to the crowd.\n\nHere are the nine ventures selected for this years full-time program:\n\n<b>Greenlight Solutions</b> teaches students and businesses to utilized sustainability options to build a better and greener future for the world. <a href=\"http://glsolutions.org/\">http://glsolutions.org/</a>\n\n<b>H.E.A.R.T. Center </b>a venture focusing on helping students with disabilities.\n\n<b>Nagi Foundation </b>hopes to promote animals safety within the Native American community. One of their goals is to promote the spaying or neutering of animals.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.glovetreat.com/\"><b>Glove Treat</b></a> creates a simple paraffin wax to help treat rheumatoid arthritis. Its quick and simple too, only taking about 90 seconds to heat the wax.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.azvisionandhearing.com/\"><b>AZ Vision and Hearing</b></a> already helps schools assess students vision and hearing, but they are creating software to back-up the program. The software will inform parents of their childs results and even alert parents if their child was not at school the day the vision and hearing test was administered.\n\n<b>Wellness lifestyle </b>has their work cut off for them when they want to make college students care about their health. But when they arent doing that, theyre promoting a healthy holistic lifestyle for all.\n\n<a href=\"http://thegeniusfactory.org/\"><b>The Genius Factory</b></a> is a tutoring and test prep center, hoping to cultivate and build students so they may succeed in their academic endeavors.\n\n<b>Zombie Box</b> created a way to greatly reduce noise pollution within city centers and housing area with their product. And with the reduction of noise pollution, they say it will lead to great success for those living within noisy communities.\n\n<b>HUYA</b> is a GPS service for the honey-do list. If theres a leaky pipe in your home, use HUYA to have a repairman over in a pinch. Its Uber meets Angies List.\n\nAfter 14 weeks, the startups will present at the Seed Spot demo day in front of a live audience filled with investors, mentors, entrepreneurs and community leaders.\n\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>','AZ Tech Beat - SEED SPOT launches 9 new startup ventures','','publish','closed','closed','','az-tech-beat-seed-spot-launches-9-new-startup-ventures','','','2015-02-19 14:42:48','2015-02-19 21:42:48','',0,'http://www.seedspot.org/?p=1448',0,'post','',0),
